 At Wed, 29 Feb 2012 16:56:02 -0500, kieron.hardy@gmail.com wrote:
 > On windows (Vista SP3 64-bit), underlines on menu item shortcut keys do not 
 > show. Shortcut keys seem to work ok.
 
 Just to make sure:
 
  * When you click on a menu, underlines shouldn't show up (which is the
    same as other Windows applications).
 
  * When you press and release Alt, then keyboard focus moves to 
    the menu bar, and underlines should show up.
 
  * If you've disabled keyboard shortcuts in DrRacket (the "Editing" ->
    "General" preference), then underlines shouldn't show up.
 
 You're seeing something different?
 
